list.name: Default
list.comment: Fixed issue with endianess, as I had not realized the functions used were byte-order, and not bit order. Also, reworked the dungeon struct to include a pointer representation, avoiding the "invalid use of flexible member" error, allowing it to be dynamically allocated when loading a dungeon, rather than needing the number of rooms to be defined at compile time. Also fixed d_HEIGHT and d_WIDTH in dungeon.h as I had the values backwards from the last assignment, which caused dungeons to be written in the wrong order. Added seperate functions for opening file and parsing file path in order to clean up code and correctly report errors. Need to implement command line args still.

task.summary: Finished project. Only things left to do are optimization of the corridor drawing to draw from the center of a room, and to connect the closest room, in order to clean up number of needless corridors drawn.
Began work on updating the corridor drawing method.
Began implementation of save method. Working mostly with proper concatentation of file path. Still need to address directory issue. See TODO.
Fixed file path issue. Added compile flags for windows and unix file systems. Still need to address directory issue. See TODO.

Began project from scratch again, implemented priority queue using simple min heap. Need to iron out issues with multiple successive removals from the heap. Could make heap faster in the future by adding alpha balancing, but not needed for now.

Began project from scratch again, implemented priority queue using simple min heap. Need to iron out issues with multiple successive removals from the heap. Could make heap faster in the future by adding alpha balancing, but not needed for now.

Dijkstra's fully implemented, reimplemented heap to use an array instead. Program has a segfault problem, seems like an array issue. Easy to sort out. Program does compile so committing progress for now. Also added proj_incl to project to keep track of commonly used headers.

Fully implemented and tested dijkstra and heap. Incorporated these into the main program by adding a --display option, which will generate, but not save, a dungeon, and then display the path graph overlayed on the dungeon as well. Added Makefile, CHANGELOG, and README to project as well. Files are ready to be merged into master.

Fixed issues with memory allocation that caused earlier version of the program to crash. Program now runs properly without crashing, however, issues with the event queue sometimes cause monsters and the PC to either not move, or move improperly. Need to go back and work on the event queue, or wait until we get to C++ so event-driven execution is easier to implement.
